text: Annemiek Jansen (born 26 September 1996) is a Dutch softball player. In 2018 she went with the under-22 national team to the European Championships. She plays with the Tex Town Tigers in the highest Dutch national league. She is member of the Netherlands women's national softball team. With the national team she became European champion at the 2022 Women's Softball European Championship. ==References== Category:1996 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch softball players Category:People from Enschede Category:Sportspeople from Overijssel Category:Sportswomen
